Trio of Middle Eastern lamb sliders with baby cos and braised shallots in housemade saffron milk buns, served with paprika-dusted chips. Accompaniments: Apostle chilli honey and dukkah-spiked burger sauce; sticky barberries with Zany Zeus Greek yoghurt and sumac; and smoky eggplant and olive muttabal with Zany Zeus feta.

The Burger Blind Date is a playful, nostalgic nod to love in all its forms, inviting guests to fall for a burger instead of a person. Inspired by the classic dating show Blind Date, diners choose their match by tasting three Middle Eastern-inspired sliders. But no peeking, you're encouraged to go on pure instinct and flavour. It’s a celebration of curiosity, surprise and the joy of following your heart (and your tastebuds). With extra touches like a Love Potion guessing game and a Wall of Notes to your younger self, the experience transforms food into adventure and connection.	

Vegan alternative: Lamb burger replaced with an Impossible patty, Greek yoghurt replaced with coconut yoghurt
